OL,6,FOn that occasion, the review said, she
OL,7,Fwas wrongly assessed as being at
OL,8,Fmedium risk when she should have been
OL,9,Fclassified as a high risk case.
OL,11,FThe officer who carried out the
OL,12,Fassessment was relatively junior and
OL,13,Fhad only been working without
OL,14,Fsupervision for a matter of weeks.
OL,16,FBethany's friend said she was worried
OL,17,Fabout the pace of the police
OL,18,Finvestigation and feared she might be
OL,19,Fkilled. Within weeks she was dead.
OL,1,Woz5~k4{$z%~s1z5jw=hw1        G15/19
